Despite not getting into Berghain last night, I feel all the Berlin love and then some!! 🇩🇪🪩💫Thank you @koeniggalerie for the opportunity to manifest “Open Casting” in your magical space and for the many wunderbar new friends 🧚‍♀️🎭 On view now until July 22nd 🥂

“The distracted modes of perception that characterize ways of seeing and being seen today provide an organizing – or better, disorganizing – logic for Zuckerman’s spirited remixes of the vast archives of both popular culture and art history. OPEN CASTING includes eight paintings and five sculptural works that reflect the New York-based artist’s unique engagement with the history of depictions of the female body by male artists on the one hand and the overabundance of visual information in the landscape of digital imagery on the other.” 🎭⚡️🪩Colin Lang, @koeniggalerie

Join us as we sit down with Allison Zuckerman (@allisonzuckerman) during her visit to Berlin for her exhibition OPEN CASTING. Drawing from an extensive archive of popular culture and art history, Zuckerman crafts visually captivating and thought-provoking pieces. The interview offers a unique opportunity to hear about her creative journey and explore the inspirations behind her works.

Really can’t believe my paintings had the audacity to crash my bachelorette!! 😱💋🌴👙

It’s an immense honor to have the @rubellmuseumdc present my first retrospective, a 2016 to 2023 survey of my work. I extend my heartfelt gratitude to the Rubell family and their team for the bold presentation of my artistic journey: highlighting turning points, discoveries, and foundational themes of feminine strength and vulnerability ever-present within my work.  
 
Special thanks to the Rubell family for their immense support and belief in my spirit, to Juan Valadez and @cberryfineart for bringing this show to life, to @kravetswehbygallery for shepherding these creations into this loving home, to @danai.loukas for making the trek from Berlin to be here, and to friends and family for lending a hand to help #freethenipple 🫶💞💋

From saying ‘I do’ with @noahchaimberg to venturing into creative discoveries, 2023 was a year filled with much joy. I am grateful for the palpable love and human connection I feel through artmaking and for the steadfast support from friends and family - old and new - who I feel forever bonded to. I maintain hope that this new year will be characterized by peace, healing, growth, and understanding. 🌟💖🎨
🤍11.18.2023🤍Thank you, Noah, for your promise to walk alongside me on this shared path, towards a frontier of ever-shifting possibility, for all the days that will come our way.
